Release 1.4.27

Prefer commit to "return FALSE;" for space, and other keys where the msymbol name is exactly one character, add a sleep for Return

Resolves: https://github.com/ibus/ibus-m17n/issues/72
(Reported on Fedora 39 Gnome Wayland)

See also this comment: https://github.com/ibus/ibus-m17n/issues/72#issuecomment-1828601107

Carlos says there that mutter currently assumes that there is never
more than only one commit on a single key event.  He suggests that I
could concatenate commit strings and commit once instead of using
multiple commits. For the problem reported in
https://github.com/ibus/ibus-m17n/issues/72 this workaround is
possible and might have no disadvantages. However, I still think that
more than one commit per key event should be allowed.

Doing only a single commit and then 'return TRUE;` avoids reordering in mutter.

That trick works well for space and other keys which have a Unicode
value, are not Control characters and when no modifiers are pressed
(When modifiers are pressed, there is no way to add that information
to the commit string).

The Return and KP_Enter key events are kind of a special case, even though
these are control characters, appending "\n" to the commit string works in
many cases. But not in all cases:

- older versions of firefox insert nothing when "\n" is committed.

- Messengers like Telegram, Zalo, ... which usually send a message
  when Return is typed don’t do that when the event is not passed
  through but "\n" is committed. Zalo inserts a space instead,
  Telegram does nothing.

- In some search entries, for example in the search entry in
  LibreOffice, passing the key event Return starts the search but
  committing "\n" does not.  In the search entry of Libreoffice,
  committing "\n" inserts something which looks like a ⏎ RETURN
  SYMBOL.

For the cases, where the trick to append to the commit string cannot
be used, a sleep of 0.1 seconds between the commit and the passing of
the key event to the application helps Mutter to guess which actions
belong together and get the order right. So this mostly "fixes" the
problem as well. A sleep is not so nice, but these other cases are
rare, so the sleep should not hurt much.

Release 1.4.24
Update ibus-m17n.pot

Use “<developer><name>…</name></developer>” in m17n.appdata.xml instead of “<developer_name>…</developer_name>”

Because </developer_name> is deprecated and it makes the build fail on Fedora rawhide.

Make IBusEngineSimple read ~/.XCompose

Resolves: https://github.com/ibus/ibus-m17n/issues/70

Do not hide empty preedit text before committing text

Resolves: https://github.com/ibus/ibus-m17n/pull/64

Together with ibus >= 1.5.29 this solves the preedit flicker
problem reported in https://github.com/ibus/ibus/issues/2536
perfectly.

Thank you very much to Takao Fujiwara for the pull request.

I rewrote it a bit to make it easier for me to understand.

Hiding preedit text before committing text causes a reset of the
cursor position.

minput_filter() sometimes causes two calls to
ibus_m17n_engine_update_preedit(), the first one with a non-empty
preedit and then a second one with an empty preedit if text to commit
was produced.  But the call to ibus_m17n_engine_commit_string ()
happens a bit later and updating the empty preedit before the commit
causes the cursor to jump left and then right again when the commit is
done (This cursor jump is not always reproducible, it depends on speed
and may be invisible).

This also reverts the b74c6a68453e5a8132c7f2c104c446c8e5604963
(the workaround for the flicker).

Release 1.4.23
Update ibus-m17n.pot

Do not translate the Multi_key when using the option “☑️ Use US keyboard layout”

Do not translate the Multi_key: If the non-US layout has a Multi_key,
trying to translate it to US layout just takes it away. Skipping the
translation keeps the Multi_key around which is more useful, it can still
be used for Compose then.

Fix option “☑️ Use US keyboard layout”

Resolves: https://github.com/ibus/ibus-m17n/issues/66

The change to the keyval of the US layout needs to be done **before**
doing the Compose support, i.e.  **before**:

   IBUS_ENGINE_CLASS (parent_class)->process_key_event (engine, keyval, keycode, modifiers)

If the keyval is not yet translated before the Compose support is
done, then the Compose support cannot work as intended.

On top of that, if a non-ASCII keyval is fed into the parent class
(IBusEngineSimple), then IBusEngineSimple usually commits it
immediately. That had the effect that when a Russian layout was used
together with the option

☑️ Use US keyboard layout

all the Cyrillic letters were committed immediately before they could
be translated into the respective key values on the US layout.

Release 1.4.20
Update ibus-m17n.pot (only line number changes)

Reduce preedit flicker: Call ibus_engine_show_preedit_text() directly before **and** after IBUS_ENGINE_CLASS(parent_class)->process_key_event()

Resolves: https://github.com/ibus/ibus/issues/2536

Seems to avoid almost all of the flicker in the preedit cause by
ibus_engine_simple_process_key_event() calling
ibus_engine_hide_preedit_text((IBusEngine *)simple) if no compose
sequence was started.
